cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation in computer vision, which involves learning a model on a source domain and applying it to a target domain with different distribution. This falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). However, given the focus on deep learning and Gaussian processes, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
